The &quot;rules of the game&quot; of international politics are very important. Before we decide on who gets what, so to speak, we have to all grant that certain modus operandi are not gonna be tolerated with terrorism being one method in that category. <br>
<br>
I think one reason why war opponents don't like such discussion is because they feel it's unfair that the US talk in such virtuous terms when, to these people at least, the US has not always acted in a way that is very virtuous. What do they mean when they point to lack of American &quot;virtue?&quot; Typically the litany starts with discussion of how the CIA undermined nationalist gov'ts in Iran, central america, south america, etc during the 1950's and into the 1970's. <br>
<br>
It's always assumed that these covert actions are &quot;bad&quot; in some objective sense. However, if you think about the stated goal of many of these operations, ie to maintain stability in these countries and the region, or to support anti-communist leaders in these areas, these goals are not &quot;Evil&quot; and are not undemocratic. They merely represent the values of a people and economic system that have proven themselves relatively more capable of meeting the basic needs of the people they've served over time. <br>
<br>
How could America be criticized for opposing communism? Has the world missed out on something grand because of American determination to contain and eliminate communism? Ask Cuba and North Koreans how their basic human needs are being met by that economic system. People everywhere, left to choose for themselves, throw off the shackles of communism. It was and is a failed social experiment. <br>
<br>
The United states has consistently opposed instability, tried to contain, and finally eliminate Communism, simply because we have experienced and reflect the experience of the majority of the world that knows that people can get better than what is offered through that political\economic system. <br>
<br>
Capitalism\Democracy may not be perfect, but it does have a profoundly better track record than other alternatives. <br>
<br>
Finally, if you don't like American values in this regard.....what is your alternative? What economic system do you intend to feed and provide for your people with? You don't like our values &quot;shoved down your throats?&quot;....what is YOUR alternative? <br>
<br>
I predict what we will find is that war opponents are really good at being against things, but not so good at alternatives or coming up with another reasonable path. <br>
<br>
<br>
